== [[Latin]] ==

=== Etymology ===
From [[Horace]], Odes I.xi.8: ''Carpe diem, quam minimum credula postero'', meaning "seize the day while trusting little on what tomorrow might bring".

=== [[phrase]] ===
# seize the day, make the most of today, enjoy the present

